title: Antennaria racemosa - racemose pussytoes
description: Antennaria racemosa growing in the open understory of mostly lodgepole pine (Pinus contorta) and some Douglas fir (Pseudotsuga menziesii). Well developed basal leaves with green upper and white hairy lower surfaces combined with Antennaria flowering heads arranged in an open panicle distinguish the understory-inhabiting Antennaria racemosa. This site lies along the Triple Tree trail up towards the overlook bench, Gallatin Range, Gallatin County, Montana.
label: Original
